overview: The user requested the implementation of a database, admin dashboard,
  and authentication for a sleep questionnaire application based on a provided
  Statement of Work. The agent evaluated the existing codebase, identified
  missing components, and created a detailed plan. Key decisions included using
  NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma, implementing a simple password-based
  authentication, and building a basic admin dashboard for viewing and exporting
  responses. During implementation, the authentication system was refined to
  leverage Next.js middleware for a cleaner and more efficient approach to route
  protection. The agent also assisted the user with database setup and
  successfully tested the API endpoints and admin dashboard functionality,
  confirming data persistence and access.
